<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-05-19T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-05-19T23:00:00-05:00" n="625" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d625">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">851.01/3875a: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Acting American Representative to the French Committee of
                                    National Liberation at Algiers</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Chapin</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-05-20T00:00:00-04:00">May
                                        20, 1944—midnight</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1574. For Murphy. We have been particularly interested in the
                                telegrams which you and Chapin have been sending on subject of de
                                Gaulle’s denunciation of Clark–Darlan Agreement and Assembly’s
                                resolution that Committee adopt name of provisional government of
                                France.</p>
                            <p>You are correct in your assumption that the question of revision of
                                Clark–Darlan agreement should be kept on military level and that if
                                new agreement is achieved it should be signed by Supreme Allied
                                Commander, Mediterranean Theater.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>